Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock scored a century (109 runs) for South Africa.
South Africa scored 311-7 in their 50 overs.
Australia was all out for 177 runs.
Kagiso Rabada took 3 wickets for 33 runs.
Tabraiz Shamsi took 2 wickets for 38 runs.
Keshav Maharaj took 2 wickets for 30 runs.
Australia's top scorer was Marnus Labuschagne with 46 runs.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia won the toss and chose to field first.
Post-Match Reflections: Pat Cummins reflected on the loss, mentioning the need to adapt to all conditions and the team's hurt after the defeat.
Temba Bavuma praised Quinton de Kock and the team's performance, calling it a near-perfect game.
Quinton de Kock, the Player of the Match, expressed satisfaction with the team's performance and emphasized taking it game by game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in Lucknow.
Australia's net run rate dropped to minus 1.85 after the match.
Australia has lost 7 of their last 8 ODIs.
